article.headline: Siena 87, Fairfield 81
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- Edwin Ubiles had 22 points and 11 rebounds to lead Siena to an 87-81 win over Fairfield and sole possession of first place in the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference. Ronald Moore added a career-high 20 points as the Saints, now 9-4 overall and 3-0 in the MAAC, notched their fourth victory in a row and 10th consecutive win at home. Kenny Hasbrouck chipped in 17 points and Alex Franklin had 15. Jonathan Han led Fairfield with 22 points and seven assists. Greg Nero had 21 points and 12 rebounds, and Anthony Johnson scored 12. Siena led 45-40 at the end of a first half that saw six ties and eight lead changes. Fairfield falls to 8-5, 2-1 in the league.
